			<noscript>
			<h2>Ingot Casting Machines used and new are built by Ingotech Casting
			Services Ltd based in the UK, Germany, Spain and Bahrain. Ingot
			Casting machines, and stacking machines in the UK and world wide.
			We provide the following products and services - low turbulence
			pouring systems which minimise oxidization, the star wheel, product
			ejection, aluminium alloys, molten metal filtration, flow control,
			solidification and conveyor chain strands. Many metals are involved
			including aluminum, Al, brass, bronze, copper, Cu, zink, zinc,
			Zn, lead, Pb and ferro aluminium. Upgrading and improving ingot
			casting machines of other manufacturers. All of which have their
			part in manufacturing and building Ingot Casting Machines. We
			are located in Staffordshire, England.</h2>
			<p>Designing Ingot Casting machinery using CAD software. Our standard
			range of pouring systems can be configured to suit existing furnace
			installations, even with low tapping heights at the design stage.
			We produce brand new designs for special purpose machines to suit
			individual requirements. Past examples include lead billet casters,
			and lead conveyors used in munitions demilitarisation systems.
			Moulds - Cast in high grade SG Iron which is melted electrically
			with on site analytic facilities to ensure and maintain consistent
			quality. We use the latest foundry techniques and high quality
			board mounted pattern equipment. We have a small range of standard
			moulds for ingot and deoxidant shapes, but the majority of our
			machines are built with customer-specific moulds. We can make
			a mould to match customers&#146; existing product lines, or we can
			design new moulds to produce stackable or interlocking ingots
			within specified weight or size limits. Pouring - Ingotech manufacture
			various pouring mechanisms, and select the most appropriate system.
			Aluminium ingot, Aluminium deoxidant shapes, Zinc and lead ingot
			and Copper and brass ingot. Construction - Standard OEM components
			are used where possible. Cooling can be achieved with either spray
			nozzles or water dip tank, depending on requirements. The knockout
			consists of mechanically actuated hammers striking each mould
			to loosen the product as it passes around the head-shaft. The
			hammers are aluminium bronze rollers to prevent damage to moulds.
			Stacking - Ingotech manufacture ingot stacking equipment for ingots,
			plates, waffles etc, incorporating automatic banding and weighing
			systems. Water cooling and recycling systems can be incorporated
			if required. Furnace Tapping Equipment - Ingotech manufacture
			and supply a range of furnace tapping spouts and control needles
			to suit various furnace wall thicknesses. Spectrographic (mushroom)
			sample moulds are made. When installed with hydraulic tilting
			furnaces, automatic control of the furnace can be achieved. Flow
			control valve needles and seats for the filter boxes are normally
			available from stock. Refurbishment - upgrading and improving
			ingot casting machines of other manufacture. Our star-wheel and
			tray pouring systems can be easily adapted to fit any straight-line
			casting conveyor.</p>
